ssmate you admire for an AHS Alumni Award  We are immensely proud of our many accomplished alumni who are forging award-worthy careers in business, nonprofit, government and academia.  We honor several each year through the AHS Alumni Awards program:   AHS Distinguished Alumni Achievement Award  AHS Loyalty Award  AHS New Alum Award   Details on each award are below. Nominations can be made at any time.  Whenever possible, the college confers at least one award in each category. Award winners are recognized during AHS CELEBRATES in spring. Honorees must be present to receive their awards.                2020 AHS Distinguished Alumni Achievement Award recipient    Grace Baranek ’81 BS OT   Associate Dean and Chair, Mrs. T.H. Chan Division of Occupational Science and Occupational Therapy, University of Southern California     See all our past award recipients        AHS Distinguished Alumni Achievement Award   Established in 1987, this is the highest honor bestowed upon alumni of the UIC College of Applied Health Sciences (by the college’s current or former names). It is presented to alumni who have attained outstanding success and national or international distinction in their chosen profession or life’s work, and whose accomplishments reflect admirably on or bring honor to their alma mater.       Nominate now        AHS Loyalty Award   This award is bestowed upon alumni of the UIC College of Applied Health Sciences (by the college’s current or former names) who have made significant, notable and meritorious contributions, and who have consistently demonstrated exceptional loyalty, commitment, dedication and service to the college and/or one of its departments for the advancement of their alma mater.       Nominate now        AHS New Alum Award   UIC College of Applied Health Sciences alumni are a wide array of interesting and accomplished people. To celebrate, we honor up to two recent alumni (graduated within 10 years) whose careers and lives are on the rise.       Nominate now              Questions?   Have questions about the AHS Alumni Awards program? Contact Keenan Cutsforth for help with submissions, details on AHS CELEBRATES and more.    You can contact me at:     Email  keenanc@uic.edu      Phone  312-996-1339      Address  808 S. Wood St., 167 CMET Chicago, IL 60612      Fax  312-413-0086               AHS Alumni    Back to main content           Give to AHS    Expand Give to AHS menu          Why Give?    Ways to Give    Where to Give      AHS Alumni Awards    Expand AHS Alumni Awards menu          Alumni Award Recipients      Meet Our Alumni    Corporate Partners Program    News    Events    Contact              Follow AHS Alumni      Facebook      Twitter      LinkedIn      Instagram      YouTube                         College of  Applied Health  Sciences       UI Health Logo                            Quick Links    Calendar    Directory    News    Inside AHS    Graduation      Resources    Academic Support and Achievement Program    Student Resources    Faculty and Staff Resources    Academic Calendar      Tools    myUIC    GoogleApps@UIC    Webmail    Blackboard    Nessie        Connect with AHS    Contact us    Apply Now    Give to AHS         1919 W Taylor St, Chicago, IL 60612  312-996-6695  ahsinfo@uic.edu    Social Media Accounts      Facebook      Twitter      LinkedIn      Instagram      YouTube                     UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC News  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield            